**AERIS Frontend**

AERIS is a location-aware environmental insight application that helps users understand the real-time environmental conditions around them.
The frontend focuses on presenting clear, actionable daily insights such as air quality status, heat risk, potential flooding conditions, surrounding noise estimation, and nearby green areas.

This repository contains the user-facing interface of AERIS, built to deliver a fast, responsive, and accessible experience across devices. It integrates location-based data, visual dashboards, and recommendation components designed to translate complex environmental data into simple, human-friendly guidance.

The frontend is structured with scalability in mind, separating UI components, data services, and environmental visualization modules so the application can evolve alongside the backend aggregation and scoring engine.

Current scope of this repository:

- Location-based environmental dashboard
- Environmental score visualization
- Daily recommendations panel
- Green area proximity display
- Modular service layer ready for backend integration

This project represents the first phase of AERIS, focusing on user experience and environmental data presentation. Backend services, aggregation logic, and scoring engines will be developed in a separate repository and integrated in later stages.
